                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                <date>Wednesday December 6<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1854</date>.</p>\n            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>\n            <p>We have been anxiously waiting for a letter<lb/> but are disappointed. Nothing new\n                has occurred<lb/> the Occident came yesterday, two weeks after we<lb/> sent for\n                them, they are ready to send away. no-<lb/>one has been to inquire after you. There\n                are a<lb/> few letters coming to the house for you, Mama<lb/> thinks they all know\n                you are absent. We received<lb/> a letter from <persName>Uncle Sam</persName> on\n                    <date>Monday</date>, he says<lb/> Mama had better not move till he comes on\n                next<lb/> summer. We wish you were back again the wea<lb/>-ther is so extremely cold\n                we are afraid you will<lb/> get sick, it snows and we can hardly keep warm<lb/> I\n                went down to <persName>Mr Martins</persName> dancing school, day before<lb/>\n                yesterday, with Mama, <persName>Mr Hans</persName>' daughters are<lb/> going.\n                    <persName>Delia</persName> is trying to learn to read. You<lb/> must excuse my\n                short letter for I have my<lb/> lessons to learn. We have a new girl she came<lb/>\n                on <date>Saturday</date>.</p>\n            <p>PS <date>Thursday 7<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">We received your letter dated the <date>2<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                    >nd</hi></date> in<lb/> the morning and the one dated the <date>7<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >th</hi></date> in the afternoon</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3h708m2d/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
