                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3h708m2d/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>They were both very <sic>ecceptable</sic>. We will attend to<lb/> the Bible. There is\n                a <sic>discontinuence</sic> from <placeName>Louisville</placeName><lb/> we have had\n                no letters for you for several days and<lb/> no money. It will come in bushels when\n                you come<lb/> home <sic>wich</sic> Mama hopes will be very soon<lb/> you must take\n                care of your self and not get frozen<lb/> up. I will look over the Map and do just\n                as you<lb/> told me   Mamas best regards and hopes you<lb/> will take care of your<lb/>\n                <persName>Delia</persName> sends her love</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">This is from your little</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Nelly Cozens</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3h708m2d/canvas/p2"
                }
